  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "The IE8 parser seems to ignore attributes on the `title` tag, losing the data-reactid:\n\n```\n>> document.querySelector('title').getAttribute('data-reactid')\nnull\n```\n\nReact will later complain with:\n\n```\nInvariant Violation: findComponentRoot(..., <reactid>): Unable to fund element.\n```\n\nI'm working around this with a small wrapper component that resets `data-reactid` attribute in `componentDidMount`:\n\n```\nvar Title = React.createClass({\n    render: function() {\n        return this.transferPropsTo(<title>{this.props.children}</title>);\n    },\n    componentDidMount: function() {\n        var node = document.querySelector('title');\n        if (!node.getAttribute('data-reactid')) {\n            node.setAttribute('data-reactid', this._rootNodeID);\n        }\n    }\n});\n```\n\nShould this be added as `ReactDOMTitle`?\n",
